  "result": "A debouncer delays firing the search until the user stops typing for a set window (e.g., 300ms), so you don't send a request on every keystroke.\n\nMain wins:\n- **Fewer requests** — one call for \"react\" instead of five (r, re, rea, reac, react).\n- **Less backend/DB load** and lower API cost.\n- **Avoids race conditions** where a slower earlier response overwrites a newer one.\n- **Smoother UI** — no flicker from rapid-fire result swaps.\n\nTradeoff: added latency equal to the debounce window. If you want instant feedback *and* fewer stale requests, pair a shorter debounce with request cancellation (AbortController).",
